# Timr – Laravel API Backend

## Project Overview
Multi-tenant SaaS REST API for shift scheduling and time tracking.
Managers create and assign shifts, employees view their shifts and clock in/out.

## Tech Stack
- Laravel 12
- PHP 8.5+
- MySQL
- Redis (queues)
- Laravel Sanctum (authentication)
- Spatie Laravel Permission (roles)


---

## Database Schema

### companies
```
id, name, slug, created_at, updated_at
```

### users
```
id, company_id (FK), name, email, password,
is_active (bool), created_at, updated_at
```

### shifts
```
id, company_id (FK), employee_id (FK users),
title, start_time, end_time, notes,
status (draft/published/cancelled),
created_at, updated_at
```

### locations
```
id, company_id (FK), name, address,
latitude, longitude, geo_fence_radius (int, meters),
created_at, updated_at
```

### clock_entries
```
id, shift_id (FK), user_id (FK),
clocked_in_at, clocked_out_at,
clock_in_lat, clock_in_lng,
created_at, updated_at
```

