## API Routes
```
POST   /api/auth/register
POST   /api/auth/login
POST   /api/auth/logout

# Manager (role: manager)
GET    /api/manager/employees
POST   /api/manager/employees
GET    /api/manager/shifts
POST   /api/manager/shifts
PUT    /api/manager/shifts/{shift}
DELETE /api/manager/shifts/{shift}
GET    /api/manager/locations
POST   /api/manager/locations

# Employee (role: employee)
GET    /api/employee/shifts
POST   /api/employee/clock-in
POST   /api/employee/clock-out
```

---

## Coding Conventions

### Multi-Tenancy
Every model (except Company) must have a Global Scope filtering by company_id.
Always verify company_id in Policies to prevent data leaking between tenants.

```php
protected static function booted(): void
{
    static::addGlobalScope('company', function (Builder $builder) {
        if (auth()->check()) {
            $builder->where('company_id', auth()->user()->company_id);
        }
    });
}
```

### Controllers
- Thin controllers, business logic lives in Services
- Always use Form Requests for validation
- Always use API Resources for responses

### Consistent JSON response format
```json
{ "data": {}, "message": "Success" }
{ "message": "Error description", "errors": {} }
```

### Policies
Always use Policies, never inline authorization in controllers.
Always check company_id ownership on every resource.

```php
public function update(User $user, Shift $shift): bool
{
    return $user->company_id === $shift->company_id
        && $user->hasRole('manager');
}
```

### Services
- One responsibility per service
- Inject dependencies via constructor

---

## Roles (Spatie Permission)
```
manager  → create/edit/delete shifts, manage employees, view locations
employee → view own shifts, clock in, clock out
```

---

## GeoFence
Use Haversine formula to calculate distance between employee GPS and location.
Throw a ValidationException if employee is outside the allowed radius.

```php
public function isWithinRange(float $lat, float $lng, Location $location): bool
{
    $distance = $this->haversineDistance($lat, $lng, $location->latitude, $location->longitude);
    return $distance <= $location->geo_fence_radius;
}
```

---

## Testing with Pest

### Conventions
- All tests written in Pest (never PHPUnit syntax)
- Use RefreshDatabase on every test file
- Use factories for all test data
- Group tests by feature in /tests/Feature/
- Descriptive test names in plain English

### Structure
```
tests/
└── Feature/
    ├── Auth/
    │   ├── LoginTest.php
    │   └── RegisterTest.php
    ├── Manager/
    │   ├── ShiftTest.php
    │   ├── EmployeeTest.php
    │   └── LocationTest.php
    └── Employee/
        ├── ShiftTest.php
        └── ClockTest.php
```

### Example Tests

```php
// tests/Feature/Manager/ShiftTest.php
uses(RefreshDatabase::class);

beforeEach(function () {
    $this->company = Company::factory()->create();
    $this->manager = User::factory()->for($this->company)->create();
    $this->manager->assignRole('manager');
    $this->actingAs($this->manager);
});

it('allows a manager to create a shift', function () {
    $employee = User::factory()->for($this->company)->create();
    $employee->assignRole('employee');

    $response = $this->postJson('/api/manager/shifts', [
        'employee_id' => $employee->id,
        'title'       => 'Morning Shift',
        'start_time'  => '2025-06-01 08:00:00',
        'end_time'    => '2025-06-01 16:00:00',
        'status'      => 'published',
    ]);

    $response->assertCreated()
        ->assertJsonPath('data.title', 'Morning Shift');

    expect(Shift::count())->toBe(1);
});

it('prevents a manager from seeing another companys shifts', function () {
    $otherCompany = Company::factory()->create();
    $otherShift = Shift::factory()->for($otherCompany)->create();

    $this->getJson("/api/manager/shifts/{$otherShift->id}")
        ->assertForbidden();
});

it('prevents an employee from creating a shift', function () {
    $employee = User::factory()->for($this->company)->create();
    $employee->assignRole('employee');
    $this->actingAs($employee);

    $this->postJson('/api/manager/shifts', [])->assertForbidden();
});
```

```php
// tests/Feature/Employee/ClockTest.php
uses(RefreshDatabase::class);

beforeEach(function () {
    $this->company = Company::factory()->create();
    $this->employee = User::factory()->for($this->company)->create();
    $this->employee->assignRole('employee');
    $this->actingAs($this->employee);
    $this->location = Location::factory()->for($this->company)->create([
        'latitude'         => 64.1355,
        'longitude'        => -21.8954,
        'geo_fence_radius' => 200,
    ]);
});

it('allows an employee to clock in within geo fence', function () {
    $shift = Shift::factory()->for($this->company)->for($this->employee, 'employee')->create();

    $this->postJson('/api/employee/clock-in', [
        'shift_id'  => $shift->id,
        'latitude'  => 64.1356,  // within 200m
        'longitude' => -21.8955,
    ])->assertCreated();

    expect(ClockEntry::count())->toBe(1);
});

it('rejects clock in when employee is outside geo fence', function () {
    $shift = Shift::factory()->for($this->company)->for($this->employee, 'employee')->create();

    $this->postJson('/api/employee/clock-in', [
        'shift_id'  => $shift->id,
        'latitude'  => 65.6835,  // far away (Akureyri)
        'longitude' => -18.1002,
    ])->assertUnprocessable();
});

it('prevents clocking in to another employees shift', function () {
    $otherEmployee = User::factory()->for($this->company)->create();
    $shift = Shift::factory()
        ->for($this->company)
        ->for($otherEmployee, 'employee')
        ->create();

    $this->postJson('/api/employee/clock-in', [
        'shift_id'  => $shift->id,
        'latitude'  => 64.1356,
        'longitude' => -21.8955,
    ])->assertForbidden();
});
```

